From 92281a666d2853c0d0cad57f693104dae179002e Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Philipp Stanner <phasta@kernel.org>
Date: Wed, 23 Apr 2025 09:53:21 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] ALSA: rme32: Use pure devres PCI
Git-commit: 92281a666d2853c0d0cad57f693104dae179002e
Patch-mainline: v6.16-rc1
References: jsc#PED-14430 jsc#PED-14297 jsc#PED-14024

pci_request_regions() is a hybrid function which becomes managed if
pcim_enable_device() was called before. This hybrid nature is deprecated
and should not be used anymore.

Replace pci_request_regions() with the always-managed function
pcim_request_all_regions().

Signed-off-by: Philipp Stanner <phasta@kernel.org>
Reviewed-by: Andy Shevchenko <andriy.shevchenko@linux.intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Takashi Iwai <tiwai@suse.de>
Link: https://patch.msgid.link/20250423075346.45907-4-phasta@kernel.org

---
 sound/pci/rme32.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/sound/pci/rme32.c b/sound/pci/rme32.c
index a8c2ceaadef5..4bf122abea48 100644
--- a/sound/pci/rme32.c
+++ b/sound/pci/rme32.c
@@ -1284,7 +1284,7 @@ static int snd_rme32_create(struct rme32 *rme32)
 	if (err < 0)
 		return err;
 
-	err = pci_request_regions(pci, "RME32");
+	err = pcim_request_all_regions(pci, "RME32");
 	if (err < 0)
 		return err;
 	rme32->port = pci_resource_start(rme32->pci, 0);
